    "description": "<p>A magical arrow of acid springs from the caster's hand and speeds toward a single target. The caster must succeed with a ranged touch attack to hit the target. The <em>acid arrow</em> deals 2d4 points of acid damage if it hits. For every two caster levels the acid, unless somehow neutralized, lasts an additional round and deals another 2d4 points each round (2 rounds at 3rd to 4th level; 3 rounds at 5th to 6th level, etc.).</p><p>The material component for this spell is a drop of acid or some type of corrosive substance.</p>",
